<TITLE> Nizami condemns Benazir killing </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 27 (bdnews24.com) - Jamaat-e-Islami chief Motiur Rahman Nizami Thursday condemned the killing of former Pakistani prime minister Benazir Bhutto in a suicide attack in the garrison city of Rawalpindi. "Such killing is unjust and condemnable in the eye of Islam and democracy," Nizami said in a statement. He prayed for the salvation of the departed souls and expressed sympathy to the members of the victims. bd
